              ["Back Strain", "Acute, follows lifting/pushing. Muscle spasm, tenderness, impaired movement."],
              ["Disc Prolapse", "L4/L5 or L5/S1. Pain radiating to leg (Sciatica). Leaning to opposite side. SLRT positive."],
              ["Spondylolisthesis", "Lower lumbar pain worse on standing. Late childhood/Early adult."],
              ["TB Spine", "Common in young. Thoraco-lumbar region. Kyphosis (Gibbus)."],
              ["Ankylosing Spondylitis", "Morning stiffness. Pain starts in low back, involves whole spine + Sacroiliitis."],
              ["Lumbar Spondylosis", "Older patients. Pain worse on movement, coughing/sneezing. Relieved by rest."],
              ["Neoplastic", "Bone pain, Pathological fractures. Metastasis from Bronchus, Thyroid, Kidney, Breast, Prostate."]
